Pan Seared Steak Recipe :

1. Pat dry – use paper towels to pat the steaks dry to get a perfect sear and reduce oil splatter.
2. Season generously – just before cooking steaks, sprinkle both sides liberally with salt and pepper.
3. Preheat the pan on medium and brush with oil.
4. Using just 1/2 Tbsp oil reduces splatter.
5. Sear steaks – add steaks and sear each side 3-4 minutes until a brown crust has formed then use tongs to turn steaks on their sides and sear edges (1 min per edge).
6. Add butter and aromatics – melt in butter with quartered garlic cloves and rosemary sprigs. Tilt pan to spoon garlic butter over steaks and cook to your desired doneness (see chart below).
7. Remove steak and rest 10 minutes before slicing against the grain.

Liquid chlorophyll is a natural green pigment found in plants, and it is often used as a dietary supplement. Here are some of the potential health benefits associated with consuming liquid chlorophyll: 

1. Antioxidant properties: Liquid chlorophyll contains high levels of antioxidants, which can help to neutralize free radicals in the body that can damage cells and contribute to the development of chronic diseases.

2. Detoxification: Liquid chlorophyll has been shown to bind to and help eliminate toxins in the body, such as heavy metals and pesticides. It may also help to support liver function and promote the elimination of waste products.

3. Anti-inflammatory effects: Chlorophyll has been shown to have anti-inflammatory properties, which can help to reduce inflammation in the body and support overall health.

4. Promoting healthy digestion: Liquid chlorophyll may help to support the growth of beneficial gut bacteria, which can improve digestion and overall gut health.

5. Boosting immune function: Some studies have suggested that liquid chlorophyll may help to boost the immune system by promoting the production of white blood cells, which are involved in fighting off infections.

However, please keep in mind that I am not a nutrition specialist. You should always consults a healthcare, professional, or nutritionist before adding any new supplements to your diet. This is simply what I use for a daily detox and what works for me.

Life is meant to be lived - 

You have to chase the things that ignite you. You have to do the things that bring you joy. You have to surround yourself with the people who bring you back home to yourself, with the people who respect you and embrace you in ways that make you feel like you are worthy and accepted and loved. You have to do the work to heal yourself, even when it hurts - especially when it hurts, so that you do not continue to approach your life within the boundary of what is heavy within you. You have to put yourself out there, and you cannot worry about what other people think, you cannot rob yourself of experience or happiness or inspiration because you are scared of how you will be perceived. You have to be unapologetic in the way that you exist here. You have to believe that your ideas, and your hope, and your being, deserve to take up space. You have to believe that you have purpose.

Because our existence is finite. And as hard as that is to understand - as hard as that can be to connect with, from time to time remind yourself that in the most human way - we are all living on borrowed time. We live as if we are promised the experiences and the potential we are chasing, we live as if we have control over what happens to us. But we don't, and that is liberating, because it is pressing - there is urgency within the lesson. It is meant to wake you up.
